<item>
            <title>[LU-9425] Turn RDMA Fragment Fix on by default</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9425</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now that fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has landed, there is a question as to whether that fix should be &quot;off&quot; by default requiring a module parameter to activate it. &#160;This ticket is a place to &quot;debate&quot; one way or the other and to change the default to &quot;on&quot; if that is what we want.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I seem to remember a concern about the doubling of SGEs using memory causing problems for LNet routers which may be memory-lean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
